description.text: This is just a better fitting big wheel than the one in this make. http://www.thingiverse.com/thing:172225

A pair of ladders that can be used as height-adjustable support when you don't need too much precision but won't want to have to measure precisely. I use it to support the middle of my notebook (when it stands on notebook legs).

Printing and using is straightforward - you just put one of the ladders upside-down on the other one.
The most complex part is fine-tuning. I think that if you have a high-definition 3D printer, you don't need any special measures, but I don't have one.
First, height increment between steps should probably be an integer multiple of layer height.
Second, I set the fill mode to perpendicular lines. That way the fixators get printed somewhat sanely. Of course, now I need to use height increment of twice the layer height.
Also, parity of layer where the stairs occur matters a lot. There is a parameter to lift all the design by a fixed amount (adding more material at the bottom).

1st thing I've ever made, so be kind. If something is wrong let me know so I can fix it, or revise a 2nd version. I will be uploading lots of lego stuff. Lots of Legos don't print right on this site, like minifigures and aren't true 1 to 1 swappable. Mine will be 100% compatible, hips legs arms hands etc. Will take requests. Vehicles and 1 print multiple piece kits coming soon !! Everything is checked with 3d print utility. Almost done with my minifigure, will show pics with real lego mini !

description.text:
Hey guys, first thingiverse upload.. so here goes. I really liked the mount that Pablogil made for his printer and decided I wanted to adapt this to suit a Hadron.
See: http://www.thingiverse.com/thing:213852 Unfortunately you can't mount it on the top plate as even just naked the rotary encoder fouls on the x-carriage limiting Z height.. no good. So I mashed this up with http://www.thingiverse.com/thing:157749 I've added some bracing and screw holes to put it together. I'm hoping it can be printed without support... test print shortly. Update: Fixed some STL mesh issues with Netfab cloud for the imported STL, adjusted some alignment to make printing easier
